reviews.text: Perfect. Historical.

Balıkesir Saat Kulesi - Balıkesir

Saat Kulesi 1829 yılında Girit’li Mehmet Paşa tarafından İstanbul Galata Kulesi’nin benzeri olarak silindir şeklinde yaptırılmış idi. 1897 yılındaki deprem nedeniyle yıkılınca, 1901 yılında bugünkü şekliyle yeniden yaptırılmıştır. Kare prizma şeklindeki bina, beyaz kesme taş ile yapılmış ve kabartma işçiliklerle de süslü hale getirilmiştir.En üst kat kubbe ile örtülmüş ve büyük bir çan eklenmiştir. Buranın hemen altındaki katta ise dört yöne de birer saat konmuştur.

Bu kadar değerli bir eserin bu kadar biçimsiz bir noktada kalması kötü olmuş. Kuleyi yapanlar ileriyi görememişler. Kilise çanı benzeri her saat başı çalması müslüman mahallesinde salyangoza benziyor bu ses değişmeli
Şehire ayrı bir hava katan mimari yapı. Ne zaman çan başlasa içimden pink floyd high hopes mırıldanmama sebep oluyor..o nedenle ayrı seviyorum.
Kültürel mirasımızın emanet ettiği güzel yapılardan birisi

Been here a few times, always have great food here. Went there tonight and it packed. Great to see! There slow days are usually Monday and Tuesday but it was a full house almost. I can't pick one item I like here, all of it is delicious. Must try for Indian food.
The Moti Mahal served a lovely lunch... the restaurant has a nice decor and the staff was friendly and efficient without being overbearing. I look forward to my next visit there.

Favorite Indian restaurant in YYC. The owner is super nice, his kids work there and the business has been in the family since 1982. We ate there again on Valentine's day and our 2 small kids had a blast on the swing greeting guests. The copper dishes are a hit and the food is remarkable. They really put a lot of effort into their ingredients and methods and it shows! Best eggplant of any Indian restaurant.

Always great service and great food! And they definitely know how to accommodate as I have a friend who is celiac and they always make sure we have food that is not contaminated for her and they are always full of recommendations.

Cheers for an awesome meal every time!
Met up for a girls night this week. The service was execellent. The sever helped me choose the best dish. Butter chicken was unreal! Everything was so delicious and made with care. Best experience!
It was really good. better than Colorado springs McDonald's.. Everything was fresh thank you

The coke machine is always broken, service is crapy, and the wait is not worth the food. You could go somewhere for better food and get it faster. If you are in a rush go somewhere else, this place is not worth it. To top it all off it is not kid friendly anymore. They have electronic devices that don’t even work half the time. I went once and a baby got run over by a high chair. NOT kid friendly at all.
My weakness! Always a crowd but worth the wait. This location one of the cleanest for being so busy.
Wow looks really nice, so modern, good customer service and they have some good deals.

Nasty food..filthy restaurant .. I am so fed up with the sorry excuse for customer service. I came in today and ordered chicken nuggets, no dipping sauce but 2 packs of mayo, they charged me for the mayo, then tried to give me someone elses food. after they handed my food to the car in front of me, they gave me the same food without replacing it. This place is a horrible location. I will never go back to this location. The sad thing is the owners could care less.

One of the best Pizza Huts in the area. First folks in so the buffet wasn’t completely out yet. Though the food that was, was absolutely delicious & hot. Staff was friendly & on top of things. Restaurant was pretty clean & well organized.
SO so ummy...and I love supporting young readers -- thanks, Hut! ...did I mention how very yummy the pizza was? Seriously. Good pizza 🥰
Love their pizza! It's the best anywhere. The service at this one is amazing, too!
Food was good and so was the service. Waitress was great also!
Pizza hut has been always the best pizza and love the salads and sauces. Great services as well.

My favourite place to hang out around here. The food here really is the best. The Kashi Art Cafe might get all the hype, but the food here is way better. The potatoe wedges are a must try! The omelettes too are amazing. And the honey dipped French toast was simply out of the world. Loved the cold coffee and the ginger ice tea. Absolute value for money!
Good ambience. Their chocolate cake is their star attractive. Their pasta is a must try. However the staff take forever to complete the orders.
I keep coming back for their cafe latte! A relaxing place to eat and good value for money. Their white sauce shrimp pasta and french toast are amazing!

Great place. Had breakfast there during our stay at Fort Kochi. Also visited for a late lunch once. 

Very good food, everything is freshly prepared so a bit slow. 

Friendly staff and great service overall.

Nice ambience with indoor and outdoor seating areas

We tried the chocolate cake, the pineapple juice,  the cold coffee and the lemon cake. All of them were really good but then I tried the french toast... That was AMAZING, the best french toast I've ever had.

I always go there for their chocolate pastries..... best they have is choco fantasy.... enjoy it hot with scoop of vanilla ice-cream..... must try when you visit there.... other things are also good there.... like their sandwiches and coffes and other cold beverages........
I love this place... Visiting this since 2012... Yes.. best things do happen over a cup of coffee...  Lots of memories for lifetime...
A nice place if you want to spend time leisurely. ( without spending too much) Ps: We ordered only a tea and coffee so no comments about the food. Service was fine.

Awesome beverage as well as food of CCD. 
Well coordinated staff ...................
Nice place to enjoy coffee. Good Environment
